---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | RelayHub"
  description="Read the RelayHub privacy policy covering form submissions, contact details, support data, analytics posture, data retention, and user rights."
>
  <section class="rh-hero">
    <div class="rh-container rh-hero-inner">
      <p class="rh-eyebrow">Legal</p>

      <h1 class="rh-title">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>

      <p class="rh-subtitle">
        Last updated: 2 June 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rh-section">
    <div class="rh-container rh-content">

      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub respects your privacy and is committed to handling personal
        information responsibly.
      </p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how personal information may be collected,
        used, disclosed, stored, and protected when you interact with:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>relayhub.tech;</li>
        <li>RelayHub services;</li>
        <li>RelayOS-related services;</li>
        <li>documentation;</li>
        <li>support channels;</li>
        <li>early access programs;</li>
        <li>community initiatives;</li>
        <li>future products and applications.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Privacy Principles</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub aims to follow the principles of:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>minimum necessary collection;</li>
        <li>purpose limitation;</li>
        <li>user transparency;</li>
        <li>local-first operation;</li>
        <li>security by design;</li>
        <li>recovery-first design;</li>
        <li>user control where practical.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        RelayHub's design philosophy seeks to reduce unnecessary dependence on
        centralised services wherever practical.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Information We May Collect</h2>

      <p>
        Depending on how you interact with RelayHub, we may collect:
      </p>

      <h3>Identity Information</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>name;</li>
        <li>organisation name;</li>
        <li>community name;</li>
        <li>contact details.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Contact Information</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>email address;</li>
        <li>support contact information;</li>
        <li>communication preferences.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Technical Information</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>browser type;</li>
        <li>device type;</li>
        <li>operating system;</li>
        <li>website access logs;</li>
        <li>basic diagnostic information.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Support Information</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>support requests;</li>
        <li>voluntarily submitted diagnostics;</li>
        <li>voluntarily submitted bug reports;</li>
        <li>voluntarily submitted feedback.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Information We Do Not Intentionally Collect</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub does not intentionally seek to collect:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>private message content;</li>
        <li>private cryptographic keys;</li>
        <li>recovery secrets;</li>
        <li>authentication credentials;</li>
        <li>personal communications unrelated to support.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        If such information is accidentally received, reasonable efforts may be
        made to remove or protect it where practical.
      </p>

      <h2>5. How Information Is Collected</h2>

      <p>
        Information may be collected when you:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>visit the website;</li>
        <li>submit forms;</li>
        <li>join an early access list;</li>
        <li>request support;</li>
        <li>participate in surveys;</li>
        <li>contact RelayHub;</li>
        <li>voluntarily provide feedback.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Why We Collect Information</h2>

      <p>
        Information may be used to:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>respond to enquiries;</li>
        <li>provide support;</li>
        <li>improve products and documentation;</li>
        <li>operate community programs;</li>
        <li>manage early access participation;</li>
        <li>maintain security;</li>
        <li>comply with legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Cookies and Analytics</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub may use cookies or similar technologies for website operation,
        performance measurement, security, and usability improvements.
      </p>

      <p>
        Analytics technologies, if used, may collect aggregated usage information.
      </p>

      <p>
        Analytics providers may maintain their own privacy practices.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub may utilise third-party providers for:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>website hosting;</li>
        <li>email delivery;</li>
        <li>forms;</li>
        <li>analytics;</li>
        <li>support systems;</li>
        <li>payment processing;</li>
        <li>marketplace integrations.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        These providers may process information under their own privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Disclosure of Information</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub does not sell personal information.
      </p>

      <p>
        Information may be disclosed:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>with your consent;</li>
        <li>to service providers assisting RelayHub;</li>
        <li>where required by law;</li>
        <li>to protect safety or security;</li>
        <li>during business restructuring or asset transfer.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Data Security</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub seeks to implement reasonable administrative, technical,
        and organisational safeguards to protect information.
      </p>

      <p>
        No internet-connected system can guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Data Retention</h2>

      <p>
        Information is retained only for as long as reasonably necessary for:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>the purposes described in this Policy;</li>
        <li>support obligations;</li>
        <li>security requirements;</li>
        <li>legal obligations;</li>
        <li>business record keeping.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>12. Overseas Processing</h2>

      <p>
        Some service providers may store or process information outside Australia.
      </p>

      <p>
        Where practical, RelayHub will seek providers that implement appropriate
        privacy and security protections.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Access and Correction</h2>

      <p>
        You may request access to personal information held about you and request
        corrections where information is inaccurate, incomplete, or outdated.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Complaints</h2>

      <p>
        Privacy concerns or complaints may be submitted to:
      </p>

      <p>
        hello@relayhub.tech
      </p>

      <p>
        If concerns cannot be resolved, you may have rights to contact the
        Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC).
      </p>

      <h2>15. Children's Privacy</h2>

      <p>
        RelayHub is not intentionally directed toward children under the age
        required to provide valid consent in their jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <h2>16. Changes to this Policy</h2>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
      </p>

      <p>
        Updated versions will be published on this website.
      </p>

      <h2>17. Contact</h2>

      <p>
        Privacy enquiries may be directed to:
      </p>

      <p>
        hello@relayhub.tech
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>